<DOC><DOCNO> AP891020-0053 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-10-20-89 0356EDT</FILEID><FIRST>d a PM-BRF--HostageMass     10-20 0133</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--Hostage Mass,0136</SECOND><HEAD>300 Attend Mass for Thee Middle East Hostages</HEAD><DATELINE>CATSKILL, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   About 300 people attended a Roman Catholicmass to mark the 1,000th day in captivity for three Americansseized by terrorists in Lebanon.   The Rev. Bede Ferrara on Thursday led the reading of passagesfrom the Koran, Hebrew Scriptures and the Bible.   Robert Polhill, 55, Jesse Turner, 42, and Alann Steen, 50, wereabducted on Jan. 24, 1987, from the campus of Beirut University.   Polhill was a lecturer in accounting, Steen a communicationsteacher and Turner a visiting professor of mathematics and computerscience.   They are believed held by Islamic Jihad, the fundamentalistShiite Moslem group that has been holding Terry Anderson, chiefMiddle East correspondent for The Associated Press, since he waskidnapped March 16, 1985.</TEXT></DOC>